            <fr:title text="Ring elements are either units or some kind of zero divisor">Ring elements are either units or some kind of zero divisor</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>proposition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R]]></fr:tex> be a unital <html:em>associative</html:em> <fr:link href="/ring-0001/" title="Ring" uri="http://localhost:8000/ring-0001/" display-uri="ring-0001" type="local">Ring</fr:link>, let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x\in  R]]></fr:tex> be any arbitrary element of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R]]></fr:tex>. Then either <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link href="/ra-000I/" title="Unit" uri="http://localhost:8000/ra-000I/" display-uri="ra-000I" type="local">Unit</fr:link> or <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link href="/ra-000E/" title="Zero Divisor" uri="http://localhost:8000/ra-000E/" display-uri="ra-000E" type="local">Zero Divisor</fr:link>.</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="/alex-nelson/" title="Alex Nelson" uri="http://localhost:8000/alex-nelson/" display-uri="alex-nelson" type="local">Alex Nelson</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>12</fr:month><fr:day>17</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><html:p>If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> is a left zero divisor, then there is a <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[y\in  R]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[xy=0]]></fr:tex>. But if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> were also a unit, then
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\begin {align*}0&=x^{-1}0\\
&=x^{-1}(xy)\\
&=(x^{-1}x)y\\
&=1y=y\end {align*}]]></fr:tex>
which contradicts the condition that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[y\neq 0]]></fr:tex> in the definition of a zero divisor.</html:p>
<html:p>The situation for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> being a right zero divisor is similar.</html:p><html:span class="qed">âˆŽ</html:span></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 

 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="/alex-nelson/" title="Alex Nelson" uri="http://localhost:8000/alex-nelson/" display-uri="alex-nelson" type="local">Alex Nelson</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>12</fr:month><fr:day>17</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>remark</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>It is important to stress that the ring must be associative. The <fr:link href="/sedonion-0001/" title="Sedonions" uri="http://localhost:8000/sedonion-0001/" display-uri="sedonion-0001" type="local">Sedonions</fr:link> are a nonassociative unital ring where nonzero elements have a multiplicative inverse <html:em>and</html:em> there are also zero divisors.</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
